HEADWORD: Compositæ
<hw>Com*pos"i*t⟦ae⟧</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
from L. <ets>compositus</ets> made up of parts. See
<er>Composite</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A large family of
dicotyledonous plants, having their flowers arranged in dense heads of
many small florets and their anthers united in a tube. The daisy,
dandelion, and asters, are examples.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Composite</ent>⟦br⟧
